text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia resinimarginea is a tree or shrub belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Juliflorae. It is native to a large area in the Mid West and Wheatbelt region of Western Australia.The tree or shrub typically grows to a height of 1.5 to 7 metres (5 to 23 ft). It blooms from August to October producing yellow flowers.
